# FocusWork

**FocusWork** is a **macOS** app for structured focus: projects, tasks, estimates, and a **Pomodoro-style** timer (work sessions, floating timer UI). It is built with **Swift** and **SwiftUI**; the Xcode project is `FocusWork.xcodeproj`.

## Code layout (where to look)

| Area | Location |
|------|----------|
| App entry / coordination | `FocusWork/AppModel.swift` |
| Models | `FocusWork/Models/` (e.g. `FocusTask.swift`, project types) |
| Persistence & vault I/O | `FocusWork/Services/TaskStore.swift` |
| Timer engine | `FocusWork/Services/PomodoroEngine.swift` |
| Main UI | `FocusWork/Views/` (`MainWindowView`, `TaskListView`, `SettingsView`, `FloatingTimerView`) |
| Floating panel (AppKit) | `FocusWork/AppKit/FloatingPanelController.swift` |
| Release packaging | `scripts/make-dmg.sh` |

## Data: Obsidian vault vs local

- **Obsidian vault mode:** User picks a vault in Settings. Projects are **one markdown file per project** under `<Vault>/FocusWork/Projects/project_*.md` with header metadata and `#fw/…` task tags.
- **No vault:** JSON in **UserDefaults** (`focuswork.projects`, `focuswork.tasks`).

When generating or editing vault markdown (tasks/projects as files), follow **`docs/FocusWork-Obsidian-Vault-Spec.md`** so files load without repair. Canonical sources of truth for parsing behavior are **`TaskStore.swift`** and **`FocusTask.swift`**.

### **Update the `Obsidian-Vault-Spec.md` file**:
Everytime when the application makeing any changes to the Obsidian markdown file structure make sure to update `Obsidian-Vault-Spec.md` file accordingly reflect the latest config.

## Agent expectations

- Prefer **Swift/SwiftUI** and existing patterns in this repo; do not assume iOS unless the code already does.
- After format or persistence changes, align **`docs/FocusWork-Obsidian-Vault-Spec.md`** with implementation if user-facing behavior changes.
